            <person xml:id="pers1345">
               <p>Mary (&apos;Molly&apos;) Francis was serving as mistress of the school for girls
                  lodged in the &apos;old house&apos; at Kingswood, when she met and married
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1343.xml"/>John Maddern</persName>, one
                  of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">traveling preachers</seg>. The couple served together at
                  Kingswood for a few years, then moved to <placeName>London</placeName>, where
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1343.xml"/>John</persName> became a
                  respected local preacher. When <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1343.xml"
                     />John</persName> died, Molly returned to <placeName>Bristol</placeName>, to
                  serve as housekeeper at the New Room <date from="1770" to="1782">1770–82</date>.
                  See A. G. Ives, <hi rend="italic">Kingswood School</hi>
                     (<placeName>London</placeName>: <placeName>Epworth</placeName>, <date
                     when="1970">1970</date>), 40, 50.</p>
